title: For Sale:  New Custom Multicam Ghillie Suit made from Propper
postcontent:
This is my Ghillie Suit I made AFTER Sniper School in 2010 for my 2011-2012 Afghanistan Deployment. I took this ghillie suit to Afghanistan and back(minus the hat, used my original hat from sniper), but I was in an SDM role instead of a Sniper role and I did not use it. I am in need of money for a firearm project thus I am selling. It took me over three months to make and I have receipts showing a total investment of over $1,000(I must keep for tax purposes). The ghillie hat was finished this year. The hat and netting were new and professionally sewn on by a local seamstress. It took me 8 hours to put the Jute on the boonie cap.

My total price is less than the price of the materials and seamstress labor alone! Making these is monotonous and time consuming! This is not a cookie cutter ghillie suit that is mass produced; this suit is intended and designed for combat operations. You will not find another one of this quality and in this condition for this price that is made by a US Army Sniper trained soldier; or one that has gone to Afghanistan and back and still in new condition... I worked out all the kinks from my actual Sniper School ghillie suit (pictured). The only thing I did not get around to is cutting air vents into it the hat, jacket and pants before I put the jute on; these things get hot in the summer. . .

This multicam Ghillie suit is NEW! (HAS NOT BEEN THROUGH GHILLIE WASH YET!) It was made from Propper brand jacket and pants! It's way more durable than the issued multicam uniforms. The canvas and netting were professionally sewn (have receipts). All seems have been Shoe-Goo'd and painted! Elbow and knee pads have been installed in the perfect position for sniper crawl. There are a bunch of tan 550 cord tie downs.

Package includes:

Multicam Ghillie Hat - Size: 7 1/4
Multicam Ghillie Jacket - Size: Medium Regular
Multicam Ghillie Trousers - Size: Small Regular Pants fits up to 34" waist.
Comes with used Heavy Duty Dickies suspenders
Black sleeping bag stuff sack that fits all (has a blown seam, but still holds suit fine.)

Note: I took the the field pictures of this ghillie suit on the 23rd of Dec. This suit works nearly year round in this area(obviously not in the snow) and in Afghanistan. I had just taken the suit out of the stuff sack, it is not normally wrinkled and stiff looking. I highly recommend that you put this suit through a ghillie wash, and remember 70% of your suit in the field should be natural veg! The last picture is myself in 2010 in a ghillie suit of the same design but built from DCUs.

$400 cash or best offer, I am in no rush to sell. I am available weekends and weekdays. I can send larger pictures, production pictures, and will meet for inspections. Please call Nate at REDACTED if you're interested.

postcontent:
The MWG 90 Rounder for the AR-15/M16

High Capacity Magazine

The MWG 90 Rounder high capacity magazine for the AR-15/M16 provides you with the finest in state-of-the-art high capacity magazine design. The 90 Rounder's innovative snail-drum design and advanced space-age materials are combined to create a very light, completely reliable, low maintenance, high capacity magazine that will withstand a level of heavy field use that would destroy a metal magazine, while weighing 33% less.

The 90 Rounder for the AR-15/M16 is designed for 5.56mm NATO or .223 Remington ammunition.

The 90 Rounder for the AR-15/M16 is designed to be close to maintenance free. Never remove the silver-gray Teflon lubricant powder. Never Use any oil-based lubricant. Never disassemble MWG products, and never disassemble the 90 Rounder for the AR-15/M16 .

The 90 Rounder for the AR-15/M16 contains small parts & springs that may cause injury if improperly released. If repairs are required, return the magazine to MWG Company for repair. Any disassembly, alteration, re-adjustment, improper installation, or misuse of any MWG product voids all warranties.

Never attempt to load the 90 Rounder into the weapon or detach the 90 Rounder for the AR-15/M16 from the weapon, with a cartridge in the chamber. Always lock the bolt back first and visually ensure the chamber is empty.

Because of its unique design, the 90 Rounder for the AR-15/M16 can be left partially loaded for an extended period of time, but never store the 90 Rounder with more than 80 rounds loaded. Leaving the 90 Rounder for the stored with more than 80 rounds loaded may damage the springs and cause the weapon to malfunction. Never attempt to load more than 90 rounds. Loading more than 90 rounds may damage the magazine.

Always avoid lethal situations whenever possible. High capacity magazines such as the 90 Rounder for the AR-15/M16 are intended to eliminate re-loading downtime for persons in unavoidable potentially lethal situations, but no product can fully protect the user from injury or death in a firefight. The knowing use of MWG products, when a potentially lethal situation could be avoided, will constitute an assumption of the known risks of engaging in a lethal situation.

LOADING 
The 90 Rounder for the AR-15/M16 must generate energy to reliably feed ammunition into the receiver at a consistent rate. As the magazine grows full, more energy must be exerted to load additional rounds. This energy is stored in a special spring & released to move the entire ammunition load during firing. It takes a lot of energy to reliably move 90 rounds of ammunition, and so it takes a lot of energy to load those same rounds. As the magazine nears capacity, the final rounds may require substantial energy to load.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom Saiga 12
postcontent:
Possible trades listed below!

I never thought I would sell this but, I just don't use it as much as I used to. This was built to shoot competitions and I now shoot in another class that does not allow a shotgun with detachable mags.

922r parts include, trigger, hammer, disconnector, gas puck, and 3 in each SGM mag. So you are covered.

I Started with a new and well tested s12 to guarantee function and reliability.

Charging handle was moved to left side to speed up charging and reloads. Charging handle is made from a Stainless steel forging and was turned down on a lathe.

Side mount was removed and all holes welded shut with reinforcement added to rear trunion.

Carrier and bolt were worked over by Pauly from Pauly's steelin. This improves reliability and allows you to reload with bolt closed on a full mag.

Magwell for SGM mags was fit and installed to allow for AR style mag insertion and release (drop free) no rock n lock like standard AK's.

Saftey and Mag release extensions were custom made and fitted. This allow for fast index finger operation improving ergonomics.

Tromix S12 trigger was used

HK style sights were installed, and XS sights inserts were used. This is a ghost ring style sight with a tritium insert.

True Thumb hole stock was used No dragnov crap here. We machined a custom butt-stock end plate so that we could install a recoil pad, you will not find this on any other S12.

Gun was blasted and coated with Norrels molyresin, a durable and true firearms coating.

If you would like to view the gun in person I currently have it at Jackson Guns and ammo in Henrietta NY.
